  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ficensa Loan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Banco Financiera Centroamericana, SA (FICENSA) was established in 1974 and since inception has focused on financing the corporate and middle market sectors in Honduras including key agribusiness operators. Ficensa&apos;&apos;s conservative business model, has enabled it to weather the recent financial crisis and show consistent profitability. It is the 8th largest bank in loan portfolio (3.3% market share) and the 11th in deposits (2.5% market share) out of 17 commercial banks in Honduras.    The proposed investment project entails a straight senior loan US$ 15 million and a US$ 6 million trade line to be used to grow the small and middle market loan portfolio.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Banking penetration: by promoting access to credit along the small and medium market companies.  Export competitiveness: by providing long term financing that can facilitate the implementation of better production tecnologies, which could eventually sustain competitive exports.  Employment generation: SMEs are a large employment generator in Honduras  and more access to credit will translate into larger production scales requiring more workers.</narrative>
  </description>
